---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import VerdictBlock from '../components/VerdictBlock.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Intervention Readiness · Can you stop it in time?"
  description="Intervention Readiness asks whether an organisation can detect, escalate, decide and intervene before harm becomes irreversible. AGDA™ measures it and signs the answer."
  current="home"
>
  <!-- 1 · DOORWAY. Loud. -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="wrap">
      <span class="label hero-label">Intervention Readiness</span>
      <h1 class="display-xl">Can you stop it <em>in time?</em></h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        AI systems are becoming more capable. Organisations are becoming more
        dependent on automation. Human oversight only matters if intervention
        remains possible.
      </p>
      <p class="hero-note"><span class="agda-mark">AGDA<span class="agda-tm">™</span></span> measures Intervention Readiness.</p>
      <div class="hero-cta">
        <a href="/Intervene/contact/" class="btn">Find out where you stand</a>
      </div>
      <ul class="hero-chain" role="list" aria-label="Intervention readiness chain">
        <li>Detect</li>
        <li>Escalate</li>
        <li>Decide</li>
        <li>Intervene</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 2 · Recognition. Quiet. -->
  <section class="block quiet">
    <div class="wrap-narrow">
      <h2 class="h2">The honest answer is usually <em>“I think so.”</em></h2>
      <p class="body">
        You have a framework. An accountable owner, documented controls, an
        escalation policy. All of it real, and all of it necessary. None of it
        proves the one thing that decides the outcome: at 3am, can the person
        who can halt the system be reached, authorised, and certain enough to
        act while acting still costs less than waiting?
      </p>
      <p class="body muted">Most organisations know what controls they have. Few know whether those controls can intervene in time.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 3 · Recognition scenario. Quiet, building. -->
  <section class="block quiet">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="window-head">
        <h2 class="h2">You have probably watched <em>a version of this.</em></h2>
        <p class="lede muted">
          Not because anyone was careless. Because systems act quickly,
          authority moves through people, and harm can become irreversible
          before governance has turned into action.
        </p>
      </div>

      <ol class="window-grid reveal" role="list">
        <li class="stage">
          <div class="chip-row"><span class="time-chip">T+0</span><span class="stage-label">System event</span></div>
          <h3 class="h3">No signal yet.</h3>
          <p class="body muted">The system starts producing decisions outside its limits. Nothing has reached anyone with the authority to act.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="stage">
          <div class="chip-row"><span class="time-chip">T+6h</span><span class="stage-label">Operations</span></div>
          <h3 class="h3">Noticed, not stoppable.</h3>
          <p class="body muted">Someone sees the deviation. They cannot halt the system, and the route to who can is unclear.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="stage">
          <div class="chip-row"><span class="time-chip">T+18h</span><span class="stage-label">Management</span></div>
          <h3 class="h3">Still compounding.</h3>
          <p class="body muted">It reaches management. Authority to halt is still being established. The cost grows by the hour.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="stage critical">
          <div class="chip-row"><span class="time-chip warn">T+36h</span><span class="stage-label">Board</span></div>
          <h3 class="h3">The window has closed.</h3>
          <p class="body muted">The board is informed. The moment for low-cost intervention has already passed.</p>
        </li>
      </ol>

      <p class="window-foot">The chain was never tested before it had to hold.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 4 · THE GAP. Heavy. The turn. -->
  <section class="gap">
    <div class="wrap-narrow">
      <span class="label section-kicker gap-label">The category</span>
      <h2 class="h2 gap-h">Intervention Readiness is the missing measurement.</h2>
      <p class="gap-body">
        Capital. Model performance. Control coverage. Incident counts. Audit
        findings. These matter. But the board-level question is simpler:
        when a consequential system turns, can the organisation detect,
        escalate, decide and intervene before harm becomes irreversible?
      </p>
      <p class="gap-realisation">
        <span>Governance</span>
        <span>Controls</span>
        <span>Accountability</span>
        <strong>You have not yet measured whether intervention remains possible when it matters.</strong>
      </p>
      <div class="gap-status">
        <span class="status-rule" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        <span class="gauge-label mono">Unmeasured</span>
      </div>
      <p class="gap-refrain">Which means you cannot yet answer the question. <em>Can you stop it in time?</em></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 5 · THE VERDICT. Climax. The only colour on the page. -->
  <section class="block verdict">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="verdict-flow">
        <div class="verdict-lead">
          <span class="label section-kicker">The instrument</span>
          <h2 class="h2"><span class="agda-mark">AGDA<span class="agda-tm">™</span></span> is a deterministic assessment of Intervention Readiness.</h2>
          <p class="body muted">
            It measures whether governance can actually intervene when
            required. The output is not a maturity score or a compliance
            claim. It is a signed verdict on whether intervention completes
            inside the harm window.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="verdict-stage reveal">
          <VerdictBlock />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 6 · CLOSE. Sparse. The refrain returns. -->
  <section class="block close">
    <div class="wrap close-wrap">
      <h2 class="close-q">Can you stop it <em>in time?</em></h2>
      <p class="close-line">Stronger Intervention Readiness supports better oversight, better decisions, and more confident deployment.</p>
      <a href="/Intervene/agda/" class="btn">How <span class="agda-mark">AGDA<span class="agda-tm">™</span></span> measures it</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* Dark advisory rhythm: doorway, quiet recognition, surface turn,
     evidence object, sparse close. */
  .hero,
  .gap {
    background: var(--paper);
    color: var(--ink);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--hair);
  }
  .hero ::selection,
  .gap ::selection { background: var(--accent-faint); color: var(--ink); }

  .hero .wrap,
  .block.quiet > .wrap,
  .block.quiet > .wrap-narrow,
  .gap > .wrap-narrow,
  .verdict > .wrap,
  .close > .wrap {
    max-width: 1120px;
  }

  /* 1 · Hero */
  .hero {
    min-height: calc(92vh - var(--header-h));
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    padding-top: clamp(80px, 13vh, 152px);
    padding-bottom: clamp(64px, 10vh, 120px);
    background: var(--paper-deep);
  }
  .hero-label { margin-bottom: 32px; }
  .hero .display-xl { max-width: 820px; color: var(--ink); }
  .hero-sub {
    margin: 28px 0 0;
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: clamp(18px, 1.8vw, 22px);
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: 0;
    color: var(--muted);
    line-height: 1.62;
    max-width: 48ch;
  }
  .hero-note {
    margin: 18px 0 0;
    font-size: 15px;
    color: var(--faint);
    max-width: 48ch;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .hero-cta { margin-top: 40px; display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 12px; }
  .hero-chain {
    list-style: none;
    margin: clamp(44px, 7vh, 72px) 0 0;
    padding: 28px 0 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--hair);
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 18px 36px;
  }
  .hero-chain li {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--faint);
  }

  /* Quiet recognition sections: large statements, generous air, no rules. */
  .block.quiet {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--hair);
  }
  .block.quiet .h2 { max-width: 24ch; font-size: clamp(32px, 4.6vw, 58px); line-height: 1.08; }
  .wrap-narrow .body { margin: 32px 0 0; max-width: 56ch; }

  .window-head { margin-bottom: 64px; }
  .window-head .h2 { max-width: 24ch; }
  .window-head .lede { margin-top: 20px; max-width: 54ch; }
  .window-grid {
    list-style: none; margin: 0; padding: 0;
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr); column-gap: 32px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--hair-strong);
  }
  .window-grid > .stage {
    position: relative;
    padding: 32px 0 28px; display: grid; gap: 12px; align-content: start;
    opacity: 0; transform: translateY(12px);
    transition: opacity 480ms cubic-bezier(0.4,0,0.2,1), transform 480ms cubic-bezier(0.4,0,0.2,1);
  }
  .window-grid > .stage::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    top: -1px;
    left: 0;
    width: 32px;
    height: 1px;
    background: var(--hair-strong);
  }
  .window-grid > .stage.critical::before { background: var(--warn); }
  .window-grid.in > .stage { opacity: 1; transform: none; }
  .window-grid.in > .stage:nth-child(1) { transition-delay: 0ms; }
  .window-grid.in > .stage:nth-child(2) { transition-delay: 120ms; }
  .window-grid.in > .stage:nth-child(3) { transition-delay: 240ms; }
  .window-grid.in > .stage:nth-child(4) { transition-delay: 360ms; }
  .chip-row { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 12px; }
  .time-chip {
    display: inline-block; background: var(--accent); color: var(--black);
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase; padding: 5px 9px; line-height: 1;
  }
  .time-chip.warn { background: var(--warn); }
  .stage-label { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.04em; color: var(--muted); text-transform: uppercase; }
  .window-grid .h3 { font-size: 21px; margin: 4px 0 0; }
  .window-grid p { max-width: 30ch; margin: 0; line-height: 1.58; }
  .window-foot {
    margin: 44px 0 0; padding-top: 24px; border-top: 1px solid var(--hair-strong);
    font-family: var(--font-sans); font-size: clamp(18px, 1.8vw, 24px);
    font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: -0.01em; color: var(--ink); max-width: 40ch;
  }
  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    .window-grid > .stage { opacity: 1; transform: none; transition: none; }
  }

  /* 4 · The gap. Heavy. */
  .gap { padding: clamp(96px, 14vh, 168px) 0; background: var(--paper-soft); }
  .gap-label {
    color: var(--accent); letter-spacing: 0.22em; margin-bottom: 28px;
  }
  .gap-h { color: var(--ink); max-width: 22ch; font-size: clamp(36px, 5.4vw, 70px); line-height: 1.08; }
  .gap-body {
    margin: 32px 0 0; font-family: var(--font-sans); font-size: 18px;
    line-height: 1.66; color: var(--muted); max-width: 58ch;
  }
  .gap-realisation {
    margin: 72px 0 0;
    padding: 0 0 0 24px;
    border-left: 1px solid var(--hair-strong);
    display: grid; gap: 10px;
    font-family: var(--font-sans); font-size: clamp(20px, 2.4vw, 30px);
    font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: -0.02em; line-height: 1.25; max-width: 34ch;
  }
  .gap-realisation > span { color: var(--faint); }
  .gap-realisation > strong { color: var(--ink); font-weight: 700; max-width: 30ch; margin-top: 6px; }
  .gap-status { margin: 48px 0 0; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 18px; }
  .status-rule { display: block; width: 72px; height: 1px; background: var(--accent); }
  .gauge-label { font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.18em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--faint); }
  .gap-refrain {
    margin: 40px 0 0; font-family: var(--font-sans); font-size: 16px;
    color: var(--muted); max-width: 48ch;
  }
  .gap-refrain em { color: var(--ink); font-style: italic; }

  /* 5 · The verdict. It stays on the same left rail; the certificate
     becomes the object on the right, not a centred interruption. */
  .verdict { padding-top: clamp(112px, 16vh, 184px); padding-bottom: clamp(112px, 16vh, 184px); }
  .verdict-flow {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 0.86fr) minmax(520px, 1.14fr);
    gap: clamp(48px, 7vw, 96px);
    align-items: center;
  }
  .verdict-lead { max-width: 52ch; margin: 0; text-align: left; }
  .verdict-lead .label { margin: 0 0 24px; letter-spacing: 0.12em; }
  .verdict-lead .h2 { max-width: 24ch; margin: 0; font-size: clamp(32px, 4vw, 54px); }
  .verdict-lead .body { margin: 24px 0 0; max-width: 48ch; }
  .verdict-stage { display: flex; justify-content: flex-start; min-width: 0; }

  /* 6 · Close. Sparse. */
  .close { padding-top: clamp(112px, 16vh, 200px); padding-bottom: clamp(112px, 16vh, 200px); }
  .close-wrap { display: grid; gap: 28px; justify-items: start; }
  .close-q {
    font-family: var(--font-sans); font-weight: 700;
    font-size: clamp(40px, 6vw, 88px); letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    line-height: 1.0; margin: 0; max-width: 18ch; color: var(--ink);
  }
  .close-line { font-family: var(--font-sans); font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.65; color: var(--muted); margin: 0; max-width: 56ch; }

  @media (max-width: 880px) {
    .window-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; column-gap: 24px; }
    .verdict-flow { grid-template-columns: 1fr; align-items: start; }
    .verdict-stage { max-width: 760px; }
  }
  @media (max-width: 560px) {
    .hero .wrap,
    .block.quiet > .wrap,
    .block.quiet > .wrap-narrow,
    .gap > .wrap-narrow,
    .verdict > .wrap,
    .close > .wrap {
      max-width: var(--max);
    }
    .hero-chain { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 14px 20px; }
    .window-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .gap-realisation { padding-left: 18px; }
  }
</style>
